Subject: [PATCH] Fix Apple Watch complication showing dashes instead of last
 value

Add fallback logic to show last known glucose value when activeContext is nil,
instead of returning nil which causes watchOS to display dashes (---).

Changes:
- Added LoopKit import for StoredGlucoseSample type
- Modified getCurrentTimelineEntry to call getFallbackTimelineEntry when no active context
- Added getFallbackTimelineEntry method that:
  - Fetches last glucose from local glucoseStore (past 3 hours)
  - Creates minimal WatchContext with glucose data
  - Uses correct WatchContext properties: glucose (HKQuantity), glucoseTrend, glucoseTrendRate
  - Generates complication template with gray tint to indicate stale data
  - Returns entry with last known value instead of nil

This ensures the complication always shows the most recent glucose reading
available, even when:
- iPhone is not connected
- WatchConnectivity hasn't delivered recent updates
- Active context expired or unavailable

The gray tint visually indicates the data may be stale, while still providing
useful information instead of placeholder dashes.

